quran[58]{c,v,t}:
  75,1,It needeth not that I swear by the day of the RESURRECTION
  75,2,Or that I swear by the self-accusing soul
  75,3,Thinketh man that we shall not re-unite his bones
  75,4,Aye! his very finger tips are we able evenly to replace
  75,5,But man chooseth to deny what is before him
  75,6,"He asketh, \"When this day of Resurrection"
  75,7,But when the eye shall be dazzled
  75,8,And when the moon shall be darkened
  75,9,And the sun and the moon shall be together
  75,10,"On that day man shall cry, \"Where is there a place to flee to"
  75,11,But in vain - there is no refuge
  75,12,With thy Lord on that day shall be the sole asylum
  75,13,On that day shall man be told of all that he hath done first and last
  75,14,"Yea, a man shall be the eye witness against himself"
  75,15,And even if he put forth his plea
  75,16,Move not thy tongue in haste to follow and master this revelation
  75,17,For we will see to the collecting and the recital of it
  75,18,"But when we have recited it, then follow thou the recital"
  75,19,"And, verily, afterwards it shall be ours to make it clear to thee"
  75,20,"Aye, but ye love the transitory"
  75,21,And ye neglect the life to come
  75,22,On that day shall faces beam with light
  75,23,Outlooking towards their Lord
  75,24,And faces on that day shall be dismal
  75,25,As if they thought that some great calamity would befal them
  75,26,"Aye, when the soul shall come up into the throat"
  75,27,"And there shall be a cry, \"Who hath a charm that can restore him"
  75,28,And the man feeleth that the time of his departure is come
  75,29,And when one leg shall be laid over the other
  75,30,To thy Lord on that day shall he be driven on
  75,31,"For he believed not, and he did not pray"
  75,32,But he called the truth a lie and turned his back
  75,33,"Then, walking with haughty men, rejoined his people"
  75,34,That Hour is nearer to thee and nearer
  75,35,It is ever nearer to thee and nearer still
  75,36,Thinketh man that he shall be left supreme
  75,37,Was he not a mere embryo
  75,38,Then he became thick blood of which God formed him and fashioned him
  75,39,"And made him twain, male and female"
  75,40,Is not He powerful enough to quicken the dead
  76,1,"Doth not a long time pass over MAN, during which he is a thing unremembered"
  76,2,"We have created man from the union of the sexes that we might prove him; and hearing, seeing, have we made him"
  76,3,"In a right way have we guided him, be he thankful or ungrateful"
  76,4,For the Infidels we have got ready chains and collars and flaming fire
  76,5,But a wine cup tempered at the camphor fountain the just shall quaff
  76,6,"Fount whence the servants of God shall drink, and guide by channels from place to place"
  76,7,"They who fulfilled their vows, and feared the day whose woes will spread far and wide"
  76,8,"Who though longing for it themselves, bestowed their food on the poor and the orphan and the captive"
  76,9,"We feed you for the sake of God: we seek from you neither recompense nor thanks"
  76,10,A stern and calamitous day dread we from our Lord
  76,11,From the evil therefore of that day hath God delivered them and cast on them brightness of face and joy
  76,12,"And hath rewarded their constancy, with Paradise and silken robes"
  76,13,"Reclining therein on bridal couches, nought shall they know of sun or piercing cold"
  76,14,"Its shades shall be close over them, and low shall its fruits hang down"
  76,15,And vessels of silver and goblets like flagons shall be borne round among them
  76,16,Flagons of silver whose measure themselves shall mete
  76,17,And there shall they be given to drink of the cup tempered with zendjebil (ginger)
  76,18,From the fount therein whose name is Selsebil (the softly flowing)